  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. The model predicts absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device operating at nominal flow rates of 3–6 L/min and rotational speeds of 2000–3500 RPM. Model Risk Level 5 applies given the direct patient-safety implication of hemolysis prediction in a life-sustaining device. All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors are addressed; seven are formally assessed and six are scoped out with documented epistemic rationale. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification covers inlet boundary condition variability and blood viscosity parameters. The intended use scope, device operating envelope, and patient population constraints are described in the Requirement and Claim nodes bound to this UnitOfAssurance. Decision: Accepted at Minimal profile.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cfd-hemolysis-absolute-prediction",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-centrifugal-pump-cfd-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-benchmark-2013",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-hemolysis-experimental-2021"
  ],
